GREEN
- normal web / tcp

GREEN (DARK) 
 - http (unencrypted web traffic)

BLUE (LIGHT)
 - DNS query (asking "what's the ip for google.com")

BLACK (with red text)
 - something went wrong (retransmission, packet loss, unstable connections, attacks "ddos") 
 - {packet never arrived, so it retransmissions the packet}

YELLOW 
 - windows machine communicating

PURPLE (DARK) 
 - TCP connections start & end (polite open and close conversation)

RED 
 - packet itself corrupted (checksum failed, data doesn't match what was sent) 
 - (packet arrived corrupted)

GRAY
 - abrupt and forced closed connection from one side.